{
  "texts": [
    "It suffices to discuss the topological junctions among simple TDLs as the general case follows from the distributive nature of the direct sum.",
    "We assume there is no topological junction (end-point) for a nontrivial TDL.",
    "This is equivalent to requiring the corresponding symmetry to be faithful, because otherwise the TDL could break, retract to nothing, and thus cannot be detected by physical observables.",
    "For two simple TDLs L i, L j, the junction vector space is Hom C (L i, L j) ∼ = C if they are identical, otherwise it's empty.",
    "For three simple TDLs, the junction vector space between two ingoing TDLs and one outgoing TDL is denoted by Hom C (L i ⊗ L j, L k)."
  ]
}